The paper discusses the issue of adaptivity in data analysis, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The use of information-theoretic concepts suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with statistical bias and control, which are topics that are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The issue of privacy in data analysis is another important aspect of the paper, which could place it under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper's focus on the analysis of data sets that are re-used across multiple studies or stages could also make it relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
